        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 23 at 12:53PM PDT by NWS Hanford CA</headline>
        <description>At 1253 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 19
miles west of North Lake Campground, or 22 miles west of Aspendell,
moving north at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lake Thomas Edison, Kaiser Point, Upper Burnt Corral, High Sierra,
Volcanic Knob, and Florence Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
